1
00:01:16,580 --> 00:01:19,856
One thing I've learned in the last seven years,

2
00:01:19,900 --> 00:01:25,258
in every game and con there is always
an opponent and there is always a victim.

3
00:01:26,260 --> 00:01:31,698
The trick is to know when you're the latter,
so you can become the former.

4
00:01:52,020 --> 00:01:54,534
How deep did you bury that shareholder, Paul?

5
00:01:55,540 --> 00:01:57,531
Deep.

6
00:02:00,220 --> 00:02:02,415
Are you sure this is a good idea?

7
00:02:02,460 --> 00:02:04,371
He has to pay us something, doesn't he?

8
00:02:04,420 --> 00:02:07,332
But you've got more money
than you could ever spend.

9
00:02:07,380 --> 00:02:09,530
That's all you think about nowadays.

10
00:02:09,580 --> 00:02:11,571
He owes me and he owes you.

11
00:02:11,620 --> 00:02:13,611
Now he has to pay.

12
00:02:13,660 --> 00:02:15,651
It's cause and effect.

13
00:03:15,260 --> 00:03:17,649
Sorry, sir, this table is closed.

14
00:03:18,820 --> 00:03:20,219
Send him up.

15
00:03:20,260 --> 00:03:23,775
I'm not sure that's a good idea, Mr. D.
He's got better. I mean, a lot better.

16
00:03:23,820 --> 00:03:25,219
All the tables are closed.

17
00:03:29,660 --> 00:03:31,651
Send him up, Paul.

18
00:03:36,380 --> 00:03:37,938
20.

19
00:03:37,980 --> 00:03:39,971
Hold on.

20
00:03:40,020 --> 00:03:42,056
I think we'll take the stairs, eh, Billy?

21
00:03:42,100 --> 00:03:43,977
You want to walk 20 flights, Jake?

22
00:03:44,020 --> 00:03:45,373
Don't be silly.

23
00:03:45,420 --> 00:03:48,492
I don't like to feel trapped. Never did, never will.

24
00:03:48,540 --> 00:03:52,692
Why should a man
do what he doesn't like to do?

25
00:03:53,740 --> 00:03:57,858
Jake, if you want to take the stairs,
we'll take the stairs...

26
00:03:57,900 --> 00:04:01,017
There's always a choice.
What's wrong with the stairs?

27
00:04:03,700 --> 00:04:05,053
Come on, you'll be all right.

28
00:04:22,380 --> 00:04:24,940
I've got to spend the next two minutes

29
00:04:24,980 --> 00:04:29,770
shaking and sweating like a crack whore
clucking for a fix.

30
00:04:30,820 --> 00:04:37,134
Should have taken the stairs,
cos it's getting very, very tight in here.

31
00:04:52,780 --> 00:04:55,419
I'm afraid it's only two at the table, Mr. Green.

32
00:04:59,860 --> 00:05:01,851
Freddy, you're done.

33
00:05:06,380 --> 00:05:08,257
Have a seat, Mr. Green.

34
00:05:09,700 --> 00:05:12,168
I hear you've done very well for yourself...

35
00:05:13,180 --> 00:05:14,977
...and against all the odds.

36
00:05:15,020 --> 00:05:18,615
They do say, the harder the battle
the sweeter the victory.

37
00:05:20,260 --> 00:05:23,536
A wise man once told me
there's only one rule in this world,

38
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:26,889
a small question that drives all success.

39
00:05:28,180 --> 00:05:33,493
The more a man invests in that question,
the more powerful that man will become.

40
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:37,214
Can you guess what that question is, Mr. Green?

41
00:05:40,580 --> 00:05:43,617
What's in it for me?

42
00:05:46,260 --> 00:05:50,139
I've been warned
if I let you sit down at this table I might regret it.

43
00:05:51,140 --> 00:05:54,337
They say you've become
very ambitious in your maturing,

44
00:05:54,380 --> 00:05:57,531
and you now wish to acquire yourself
a business,

45
00:05:58,580 --> 00:06:00,775
a business like my business?

46
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:03,209
But we both know what you are, don't we, Jake?

47
00:06:03,260 --> 00:06:07,776
You're a man who needs a master.
You're an employee.

48
00:06:07,820 --> 00:06:09,811
So, what's in it for me?

49
00:06:10,820 --> 00:06:14,654
The pleasure of doing an old employee a favor,

50
00:06:14,700 --> 00:06:19,251
by reminding him of the position
nature chose for him.

51
00:06:20,300 --> 00:06:22,689
Rade, how much have you got?

52
00:06:23,740 --> 00:06:25,537
What's that got to do with you?

53
00:06:25,580 --> 00:06:27,969
Toss you for it.

54
00:06:29,580 --> 00:06:31,889
He's got you there, Rade.

55
00:06:34,580 --> 00:06:37,492
It's not worth a heart attack. Get on with it.

56
00:06:40,580 --> 00:06:43,048
I'll toss you for a tenth.

57
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:46,775
You're a risk-taker of the highest caliber,
ain't you, Rade?

58
00:06:48,700 --> 00:06:50,691
I'll take red.

59
00:06:56,900 --> 00:07:02,020
Very impressive, Mr. Green.
You've honed those talents most skillfully.

60
00:07:02,060 --> 00:07:04,654
Pay the man his money, Billy.

61
00:07:04,700 --> 00:07:06,531
Should have bet the whole lot, Rade.

62
00:07:07,780 --> 00:07:10,089
You have to teach me that trick sometime.

63
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:15,811
You're on.

64
00:07:18,140 --> 00:07:20,893
I'll toss you for everything under your chin.

65
00:07:24,260 --> 00:07:26,728
There isn't a problem is there, Mr. D?

66
00:07:28,780 --> 00:07:32,136
You've got a big mouth on a small head,
sunshine.

67
00:07:34,180 --> 00:07:35,977
Be my guest.

68
00:07:36,980 --> 00:07:38,732
I'll take purple.

69
00:07:38,780 --> 00:07:40,771
You're on.

70
00:07:43,620 --> 00:07:45,576
It's a lovely color, purple,

71
00:07:45,620 --> 00:07:50,569
discretely sandwiched within
the color spectrum between blue and white.

72
00:07:51,140 --> 00:07:53,335
Always a royal winner.

73
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:02,855
Billy, do the honors.

74
00:08:03,940 --> 00:08:06,408
Don't you fucking move.

75
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:11,055
Don't let your mouth put you in more trouble
than your body could handle.

76
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:14,695
I'll tell you what I'll do.
I'll exercise a bit of charity.

77
00:08:14,740 --> 00:08:16,935
Double or quits?

78
00:08:24,780 --> 00:08:26,736
You're on.

79
00:08:28,540 --> 00:08:29,689
Come on.

80
00:08:31,340 --> 00:08:35,652
Mr. Green, Mr. Macha would appreciate it
if you came back to the table.

81
00:08:38,140 --> 00:08:40,131
I haven't finished with him yet.

82
00:08:42,980 --> 00:08:44,971
Now would be a good time.

83
00:08:46,380 --> 00:08:48,655
I think it's time to fly, don't you, Jake?

84
00:08:54,060 --> 00:08:56,051
- Excuse me.
- We're coming through here.

85
00:08:56,100 --> 00:08:59,615
Relax. You're in trouble, Mr. Green.
We could help.

86
00:09:00,660 --> 00:09:02,651
Thank you.

87
00:09:06,340 --> 00:09:09,093
I take the stairs.

88
00:10:20,940 --> 00:10:22,931
He got lucky, Mr. D, that's all.

89
00:10:22,980 --> 00:10:24,971
Fuck luck, the man's a danger.

90
00:10:25,020 --> 00:10:28,330
Since he's been out, he's made a fortune, Mr. D.
He's fat and comfortable.

91
00:10:28,380 --> 00:10:31,770
He's got what he wanted.
I'm sure we won't be hearing from him again.

92
00:10:31,820 --> 00:10:35,096
He ate seven years, Paul.
Seven years doesn't taste nice.

93
00:10:35,140 --> 00:10:38,132
Not to mention the accident
with his brother's wife.

94
00:10:41,380 --> 00:10:45,293
And what the fuck does
"I haven't finished with him yet" mean?

95
00:10:50,580 --> 00:10:52,571
Get rid of him.

96
00:10:53,580 --> 00:10:55,571
And I don't want any mistakes.

97
00:10:55,620 --> 00:10:59,010
No crackheads with sharp sticks
acting like silly fucking gangsters.

98
00:10:59,060 --> 00:11:03,258
You take Sorter and Slim Biggins.
You do it quickly, you do it quietly.

99
00:11:03,660 --> 00:11:06,128
We don't know what caused the blackout.

100
00:11:06,180 --> 00:11:10,856
But we've run some blood tests
and we'll have the results within a few hours.

101
00:11:11,860 --> 00:11:14,977
It's a miracle
you didn't sustain any damage from your fall.

102
00:11:15,020 --> 00:11:16,419
Can I go now?

103
00:11:16,460 --> 00:11:18,530
Once you've put your clothes back on.

104
00:11:18,580 --> 00:11:20,650
We'll call you back with the results.

105
00:11:21,660 --> 00:11:23,935
All right, look, I'll take your man back.

106
00:11:24,980 --> 00:11:26,971
Billy. You go home.

107
00:11:27,020 --> 00:11:29,011
It's late.

108
00:11:31,180 --> 00:11:33,171
Go easy now, yeah?

109
00:12:13,100 --> 00:12:15,330
Joe.

110
00:12:15,380 --> 00:12:16,130
Joe.

111
00:12:16,180 --> 00:12:18,375
Jake. Move.
- Joe.

112
00:12:18,420 --> 00:12:20,058
Move. Get the hell out of here.

113
00:12:28,220 --> 00:12:30,017
Al, drive the fucking car.

114
00:12:31,380 --> 00:12:32,574
Sit down and hold on.

115
00:12:41,540 --> 00:12:42,893
Get in the car.

116
00:12:45,100 --> 00:12:47,933
If I wanted you dead,
I would have shot you already.

117
00:12:53,180 --> 00:12:54,499
Sit back and be quiet.

118
00:13:06,980 --> 00:13:08,971
What?

119
00:13:09,020 --> 00:13:10,817
He missed?

120
00:13:12,380 --> 00:13:14,940
Sorter never fucking misses.

121
00:13:14,980 --> 00:13:17,653
I don't know what happened.

122
00:13:17,700 --> 00:13:19,895
Something went wrong.

123
00:13:19,940 --> 00:13:21,931
I had him in my sights...

124
00:13:21,980 --> 00:13:23,493
three times.

125
00:13:25,580 --> 00:13:27,810
You never miss, let alone three times.

126
00:13:28,860 --> 00:13:31,135
Somebody told him we was coming.

127
00:13:34,580 --> 00:13:36,855
Something is very wrong here.

128
00:13:36,900 --> 00:13:39,016
Yeah, something's fucking wrong all right.

129
00:13:39,860 --> 00:13:41,851
Don't make me angry, Slim.

130
00:13:42,940 --> 00:13:47,138
I might have missed him,
but I ain't going to miss you, not at this range.

131
00:13:49,940 --> 00:13:51,931
Maybe it's better you just drive.

132
00:13:56,380 --> 00:13:59,611
Doreen, Mr. Green. Mr. Green, Doreen.

133
00:13:59,660 --> 00:14:01,571
Good morning, Mr. Green.

134
00:14:04,580 --> 00:14:07,731
Avi, Mr. Green.

135
00:14:07,780 --> 00:14:10,817
Mr. Green, Avi.

136
00:14:10,860 --> 00:14:12,737
Sit down.

137
00:14:19,540 --> 00:14:21,531
I gather you're quite the player?

138
00:14:23,260 --> 00:14:27,219
I'm a bit of an enthusiast myself.
I thought maybe we could have a few games.

139
00:14:27,260 --> 00:14:30,536
I think you should tell me what is going on,
don't you?

140
00:14:32,780 --> 00:14:35,453
We have your medical results from the hospital.

141
00:14:35,500 --> 00:14:38,253
It's not important how we got them.

142
00:14:38,300 --> 00:14:42,339
What is important, however,
is what it has to say.

143
00:14:46,380 --> 00:14:49,929
You will die within three days
from a very unpleasant ailment

144
00:14:49,980 --> 00:14:52,289
that contaminates your blood and organs.

145
00:14:59,380 --> 00:15:03,055
Thanks, fellas.
I'll get back to you on this one, yeah?

146
00:15:04,820 --> 00:15:06,617
Mr. Green.

147
00:15:07,660 --> 00:15:10,572
30 seconds, and you can be on your way.

148
00:15:10,620 --> 00:15:13,498
The longer you listen, the sweeter the pitch.

149
00:15:13,540 --> 00:15:15,371
30 seconds?

150
00:15:26,460 --> 00:15:30,373
We've already saved your life once.
The next time will not be for free.

151
00:15:31,620 --> 00:15:34,134
We shall assist you under two conditions.

152
00:15:34,180 --> 00:15:36,740
These conditions are not negotiable.

153
00:15:36,780 --> 00:15:39,578
Oh, I'm being grafted.

154
00:15:39,620 --> 00:15:40,973
Condition one.

155
00:15:43,580 --> 00:15:45,571
We will bleed you dry.

156
00:15:45,620 --> 00:15:49,056
You have to put on a better shirt
before you bleed me dry, my friend.

157
00:15:49,100 --> 00:15:52,695
You will give us every penny you have got.

158
00:15:52,740 --> 00:15:55,015
This is a con.

159
00:15:55,060 --> 00:15:58,496
It's only natural that you think that
you are somehow being conned,

160
00:15:58,540 --> 00:16:02,169
but think a little harder,
and you will realize that this is not a trick.

161
00:16:02,220 --> 00:16:05,018
Now, condition two.

162
00:16:06,060 --> 00:16:09,894
You will do as we tell you without argument.

163
00:16:09,940 --> 00:16:15,298
This includes
answering any questions that are asked.

164
00:16:15,340 --> 00:16:20,778
You don't have a lot of time,
and, in reality, you don't have a choice.

165
00:16:22,580 --> 00:16:26,539
Now, the most sensible thing to do
would be to get a second opinion.

166
00:16:27,580 --> 00:16:29,571
Macha has unleashed his legions.

167
00:16:29,620 --> 00:16:32,851
We can protect you from the dangers you face.
That is our deal.

168
00:16:35,860 --> 00:16:39,535
You have three hours to decide.
After that, you will be beyond our help.

169
00:16:39,580 --> 00:16:42,458
Think I'm going to part with
my hard-earned cash

170
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:44,730
for a set of home-made hospital results?

171
00:16:44,780 --> 00:16:46,771
I don't think so.

172
00:16:46,820 --> 00:16:48,697
Not today.

173
00:17:01,980 --> 00:17:05,655
I don't have good news, I'm afraid, Mr. Green.

174
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:09,613
They've thought this one through all right.
Oh, they're smart.

175
00:17:09,660 --> 00:17:12,891
Smart as a pair of a little boy's shoes.

176
00:17:13,940 --> 00:17:15,931
She has to be in on it.

177
00:17:15,980 --> 00:17:17,971
That's how they got the results.

178
00:17:18,020 --> 00:17:20,898
Got to find someone they couldn't have got to.

179
00:17:21,940 --> 00:17:24,215
Well, Jake...

180
00:17:30,180 --> 00:17:32,171
I'm sorry, there's...

181
00:17:32,220 --> 00:17:34,211
there's no easy way to tell you this.

182
00:17:34,260 --> 00:17:37,696
You have a rare blood disease.

183
00:17:41,980 --> 00:17:43,971
How did they get to him?

184
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:46,777
He's in on it.

185
00:17:47,620 --> 00:17:49,099
After a few days I think...

186
00:17:50,180 --> 00:17:53,058
- How much did they pay you?
- What? Who?

187
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:54,135
How much?

188
00:17:54,180 --> 00:17:56,899
What are you talking about?
I have no idea what you mean.

189
00:17:56,940 --> 00:17:59,693
You've got five seconds. Five...

190
00:17:59,740 --> 00:18:02,174
I have no idea what you're talking about.

191
00:18:02,220 --> 00:18:03,972
- Four...
- Wh? I...

192
00:18:04,020 --> 00:18:06,329
- Three... Two...
- I don't know what you mean.

193
00:18:06,380 --> 00:18:08,018
God. No, no.

194
00:18:09,060 --> 00:18:12,735
When you're winning,
who thinks about losing?

195
00:18:12,780 --> 00:18:16,568
But when you're faced with what I'm looking at,

196
00:18:16,620 --> 00:18:20,249
a new and cold reality dawns.

197
00:18:21,580 --> 00:18:25,129
A fact we like to ignore.

198
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:27,740
You can not win.

199
00:18:27,780 --> 00:18:31,534
The only prize they guarantee
when you play this game

200
00:18:31,580 --> 00:18:33,571
is that you will lose.

201
00:18:35,580 --> 00:18:38,174
It's only a question of when.

202
00:18:40,180 --> 00:18:43,411
I made a mistake.

203
00:18:43,460 --> 00:18:48,250
You never miss,
so why now and why three times?

204
00:18:51,340 --> 00:18:53,535
I had a bad feeling.

205
00:18:56,420 --> 00:18:58,456
"Feeling?"

206
00:18:59,700 --> 00:19:03,659
I'm not sure if I paid you to have feelings,
now, did I, Sorter?

207
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:08,932
I paid you
because you're the best in the business.

208
00:19:08,980 --> 00:19:13,576
Why would you let feelings
confuse that relationship?

209
00:19:14,620 --> 00:19:16,531
Listen to me.

210
00:19:17,580 --> 00:19:20,697
Urgency has become something of an issue.

211
00:19:20,740 --> 00:19:24,130
So if you could restrain those feelings

212
00:19:24,180 --> 00:19:30,050
until you've completed the mission,
I would be most grateful.

213
00:19:31,700 --> 00:19:33,850
Do you think you could do that for me?

214
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:35,777
Sure.

215
00:19:35,820 --> 00:19:37,811
I'd appreciate it.

216
00:19:53,660 --> 00:19:58,814
If there is one thing I have learnt
about experts, they're experts on fuck all.

217
00:19:59,860 --> 00:20:04,650
If there's a rule, you can bend it.
If there's a law, it can be broken.

218
00:20:05,660 --> 00:20:13,419
From now on, I am breaking all the rules,
because desperate men do desperate deeds.

219
00:20:14,780 --> 00:20:17,374
Cash just seems to remain king, doesn't it?

220
00:20:18,820 --> 00:20:21,414
New bills. Not too many of them in this town.

221
00:20:31,260 --> 00:20:33,057
I love a new bill.

222
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:36,410
Represents so much hope.
Look how clean and stiff it is.

223
00:20:38,380 --> 00:20:40,530
It even smells proud.

224
00:20:40,580 --> 00:20:44,892
Your work starts now. You'll be driving.

225
00:20:48,060 --> 00:20:55,057
We are, and I apologize for the
unnecessarily dramatic moniker, loan sharks.

226
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:59,810
People hate and fear us,
just like you will learn to hate and fear us.

227
00:20:59,860 --> 00:21:01,976
We know how much you love a dollar bill,

228
00:21:02,020 --> 00:21:06,138
and it won't be easy watching them
fall through your hands,

229
00:21:06,180 --> 00:21:09,172
because it will be your money
that we will be loaning.

230
00:21:19,220 --> 00:21:21,211
Don't say a word.

231
00:21:22,260 --> 00:21:25,172
Just hold the bag
and if we nod, leave it on the table.

232
00:21:26,260 --> 00:21:28,251
There's nothing left.

233
00:21:29,420 --> 00:21:33,333
That's a very sad story, Mr. Horowitz.
My sympathies are with you and your colleague.

234
00:21:33,380 --> 00:21:37,612
Maybe I am being conned,
maybe I am being fooled.

235
00:21:37,660 --> 00:21:41,858
Excuse us for having to know
the reason for your loan,

236
00:21:41,900 --> 00:21:44,619
but we have to assess our clients very carefully.

237
00:21:44,660 --> 00:21:49,336
They say the sentence has been passed,
the certificate signed, so what's the point?

238
00:21:49,380 --> 00:21:52,577
The point is, this is the only option.

239
00:21:57,340 --> 00:22:01,413
If you snap those fingers at me again,
I'll fucking break 'em.

240
00:22:04,700 --> 00:22:06,736
You know our rates, right?

241
00:22:08,340 --> 00:22:09,853
And our policies?

242
00:22:11,900 --> 00:22:14,892
No offence, gentlemen,
but you have a reputation.

243
00:22:17,940 --> 00:22:20,454
I wouldn't be speaking to you if I had a choice.

244
00:22:25,740 --> 00:22:31,019
It's a strange thing,
but I still don't like to give it away.

245
00:22:33,780 --> 00:22:37,978
I know I can't take it with me, so why the pain?

246
00:22:38,980 --> 00:22:41,494
Why the fuck does it still hurt?

247
00:22:50,180 --> 00:22:54,332
And greasing the sheaths of these two pricks
isn't making it any easier.

248
00:23:06,980 --> 00:23:09,130
We need to know your history with Macha.

249
00:23:10,180 --> 00:23:12,296
How much of it?

