- One.
- One.

783
01:05:32,972 --> 01:05:38,410
So, how exactly did this "one"
manage to disarm and overpower

784
01:05:38,452 --> 01:05:41,808
a four-time national body-building champion,

785
01:05:44,572 --> 01:05:51,205
drag him half a block, throw him over a six-foot
wall and then get him to eat his own gun?

786
01:05:56,772 --> 01:05:58,444
Get down, boss.

787
01:05:59,332 --> 01:06:01,323
Just find the gunman.

788
01:06:02,572 --> 01:06:04,688
Don't fucking move.

789
01:06:04,732 --> 01:06:06,529
Lou. Lou.

790
01:06:07,812 --> 01:06:10,246
- Keep the boss down.
- What the fuck's going on?

791
01:06:13,012 --> 01:06:14,843
I don't know.

792
01:06:14,892 --> 01:06:17,201
Sorter just shot the...

793
01:06:19,412 --> 01:06:21,482
...and he went in the kitchen.

794
01:06:21,532 --> 01:06:24,046
- Nobody fucking move.
- Bastard.

795
01:06:31,412 --> 01:06:33,243
Keep the fucking boss down.

796
01:08:50,092 --> 01:08:52,208
She shot my finger off.

797
01:08:52,252 --> 01:08:54,129
The bitch shot my finger off.

798
01:09:03,652 --> 01:09:05,643
Who is it?

799
01:09:10,292 --> 01:09:11,725
Happy Tony, Lord John's man.

800
01:09:12,772 --> 01:09:15,605
Not looking so happy now, is he?

801
01:09:20,372 --> 01:09:22,090
Check she's dead, Lou.

802
01:09:22,932 --> 01:09:24,968
Greed gets them all in the end.

803
01:09:30,052 --> 01:09:32,088
Now, shoot straight, Sorter.

804
01:09:32,132 --> 01:09:34,771
Glad to see you've got those feelings in check.

805
01:09:41,932 --> 01:09:46,960
Find a couple of Lord John's boys and
persuade them to tell you where my powder is.

806
01:11:16,332 --> 01:11:19,130
What is the first rule of any game, Mr. Green?

807
01:11:21,132 --> 01:11:24,727
The only way to get smarter
is by playing a smarter opponent.

808
01:11:24,772 --> 01:11:27,366
What's rule two of any game?

809
01:11:27,412 --> 01:11:31,166
The more sophisticated the game,
the more sophisticated the opponent.

810
01:11:32,212 --> 01:11:34,806
Almost the same,
but where does it stop, Mr. Green?

811
01:11:35,852 --> 01:11:38,082
Where does this game stop?

812
01:11:38,132 --> 01:11:40,851
It stops when you start to give me answers.

813
01:11:40,892 --> 01:11:43,201
Don't let them play head games with you, Jake.

814
01:11:43,252 --> 01:11:45,925
Is it me that's playing head games with you,
Mr. Green?

815
01:11:53,332 --> 01:11:56,483
You've heard their voice for so long,
you believe it to be you.

816
01:11:58,412 --> 01:12:00,972
You believe it to be your best friend.

817
01:12:01,572 --> 01:12:04,723
They should believe
their opponent to be their best friend.

818
01:12:04,772 --> 01:12:07,366
Where's the best place
an opponent should hide?

819
01:12:09,052 --> 01:12:11,930
In the very last place you would ever look.

820
01:12:11,972 --> 01:12:15,567
Do you know who Sam Gold is, Mr. Green?

821
01:12:15,612 --> 01:12:17,603
You should,

822
01:12:17,652 --> 01:12:20,325
because he knows who you are.

823
01:12:20,372 --> 01:12:22,169
The Gold,

824
01:12:22,212 --> 01:12:24,009
Sam Gold.

825
01:12:24,052 --> 01:12:25,724
Mr. Clandestine.

826
01:12:25,772 --> 01:12:27,569
Mr. Ambiguous.

827
01:12:27,612 --> 01:12:29,921
Mr. Mystery.

828
01:12:29,972 --> 01:12:31,963
He's all up here,

829
01:12:33,012 --> 01:12:34,923
pretending to be you.

830
01:12:34,972 --> 01:12:37,327
No-one sees Gold,

831
01:12:37,372 --> 01:12:39,681
but Gold sees everything.

832
01:12:39,732 --> 01:12:41,723
You're in a game, Jake.

833
01:12:41,772 --> 01:12:43,763
You're in the game.

834
01:12:44,812 --> 01:12:46,803
Everyone's in his game,

835
01:12:46,852 --> 01:12:48,843
and nobody knows it.

836
01:12:48,892 --> 01:12:52,965
And all of this, this is his world.

837
01:12:53,012 --> 01:12:54,445
He owns it.

838
01:12:55,492 --> 01:12:57,687
He controls it.

839
01:12:57,732 --> 01:13:00,724
I've had enough of this shit.
Tell him you've had enough.

840
01:13:00,772 --> 01:13:02,364
He tells you what to do...

841
01:13:02,412 --> 01:13:04,880
- Look, that's enough.
...and when to do it.

842
01:13:04,932 --> 01:13:08,129
- Tell him.
- I said that's enough, Avi.

843
01:13:08,172 --> 01:13:12,245
Eventually, when the opponent
is challenged or questioned,

844
01:13:12,292 --> 01:13:16,570
it means the victim's investment
and thus his intelligence is questioned.

845
01:13:17,572 --> 01:13:19,290
No-one can accept that,

846
01:13:20,332 --> 01:13:22,368
not even to themselves.

847
01:13:24,812 --> 01:13:27,690
He's behind all the pain there ever was.

848
01:13:29,812 --> 01:13:32,929
Behind every crime ever committed.

849
01:13:38,292 --> 01:13:44,731
How can I be behind all the pain,
all the crime, if I don't even exist?

850
01:13:44,772 --> 01:13:50,847
And right now,
he's telling you that he doesn't even exist.

851
01:13:53,172 --> 01:13:57,450
No-one lives and displeases Gold.

852
01:13:57,492 --> 01:13:59,403
No-one but your two friends.

853
01:14:00,452 --> 01:14:04,047
We just put you to war
with the only enemy that ever existed,

854
01:14:04,092 --> 01:14:07,129
and you, you think he's your best friend.

855
01:14:07,172 --> 01:14:11,882
And they will protect their best friend
with everything they've got.

856
01:14:12,932 --> 01:14:15,810
You're protecting him, Mr. Green,

857
01:14:17,932 --> 01:14:19,923
