858
01:14:19,972 --> 01:14:22,884
Where's the best place
an opponent should hide?

859
01:14:25,292 --> 01:14:27,408
In the very last place you'd ever look.

860
01:14:27,452 --> 01:14:30,410
He's hiding behind your pain, Jake.

861
01:14:34,932 --> 01:14:37,048
You're protecting him with your pain.

862
01:14:38,052 --> 01:14:43,046
Embrace the pain and you will win this game.

863
01:14:45,252 --> 01:14:50,770
And I know nothing hurts more
than humiliation and a little money loss.

864
01:14:50,812 --> 01:14:54,043
If you change the rules on what controls you...

865
01:14:54,092 --> 01:14:58,005
...you will change the rules
on what you can control.

866
01:14:59,012 --> 01:15:02,368
How radical are you prepared to be, Mr. Green?

867
01:15:25,532 --> 01:15:28,888
The more power
you think you have in Gold's world,

868
01:15:28,932 --> 01:15:31,890
the less power you have in the real world.

869
01:15:34,572 --> 01:15:36,563
You are still in prison, Jake.

870
01:15:36,612 --> 01:15:39,604
In fact, you never left.

871
01:15:39,652 --> 01:15:43,850
Remember who they are, Jake.
Head tricksters, word slicksters.

872
01:15:43,892 --> 01:15:46,406
You wanted answers and they gave you riddles.

873
01:15:46,452 --> 01:15:49,922
You know the rules,
the longer you listened, the sweeter the pitch.

874
01:15:49,972 --> 01:15:53,044
He's got all the tricks and all the right answers.

875
01:15:54,372 --> 01:15:58,888
Don't let them do this to you, Jake.
Don't let them turn you against you.

876
01:16:01,772 --> 01:16:05,651
You don't give because it's good.
You give because it hurts him.

877
01:16:26,212 --> 01:16:28,203
What are we doing here?

878
01:16:29,212 --> 01:16:31,806
He's the enemy, Jake, not me.

879
01:16:31,852 --> 01:16:35,686
Use your perceived enemy
to destroy your real enemy.

880
01:16:35,732 --> 01:16:39,247
Do not listen, Jake.
You've got a gun. Use it.

881
01:16:40,652 --> 01:16:42,608
Don't wake him up. Suffocate him.

882
01:16:42,652 --> 01:16:45,644
Put the pillow over his head and suffocate him.

883
01:16:45,692 --> 01:16:48,331
He'd do it to you, Jake.

884
01:16:48,372 --> 01:16:51,091
If you can't do it, then you're not a free man.

885
01:16:51,132 --> 01:16:53,407
You are controlled.

886
01:16:53,452 --> 01:16:55,966
"Controlled? Free man?"

887
01:16:56,012 --> 01:16:58,367
Jake, wake up.

888
01:17:07,132 --> 01:17:11,523
Look, Mr. Macha, I'm very sorry
to have woken you. Please listen to me.

889
01:17:13,732 --> 01:17:16,246
Who's that? Mr. Green?

890
01:17:16,292 --> 01:17:20,604
Mr. Macha, please, I'm sorry to have woken you.
Listen to me.

891
01:17:20,652 --> 01:17:22,961
"Sorry." Listen at how you sound.

892
01:17:24,332 --> 01:17:26,084
I came to apologize.

893
01:17:26,132 --> 01:17:30,011
Forgive me for the things I've said
and for cheating you out of your money.

894
01:17:30,052 --> 01:17:31,804
I couldn't think clearly.

895
01:17:31,852 --> 01:17:34,047
- Shut up.
- No, no, that's too much.

896
01:17:34,092 --> 01:17:38,085
Shoot the fucker. Shoot him.
He's been trying to kill you.

897
01:17:38,132 --> 01:17:41,124
He killed your friend, shot like a fucking dog.

898
01:17:42,172 --> 01:17:45,801
That's better, Jake, in control again.
Do the right thing.

899
01:17:45,852 --> 01:17:48,730
Take care of your enemy, take care of business.

900
01:17:48,772 --> 01:17:53,288
Use any means possible
to induce head pain, and engage the enemy.

901
01:17:53,332 --> 01:17:55,129
Shut up.

902
01:17:55,172 --> 01:17:58,005
Wake up, Jake.
What are you fucking doing?

903
01:17:58,052 --> 01:18:00,043
Leave it.

904
01:18:00,092 --> 01:18:02,083
You're groveling.

905
01:18:02,132 --> 01:18:05,363
I now realize you're a man
to be feared and respected.

906
01:18:09,052 --> 01:18:11,964
I now realize you're a man
to be feared and respected.

907
01:18:12,012 --> 01:18:13,843
Stop groveling.

908
01:18:15,732 --> 01:18:17,723
Where's your pride?

909
01:18:24,292 --> 01:18:25,566
Where's your pride?

910
01:18:25,612 --> 01:18:28,410
I made a big mistake, Mr. Macha.
Shut up.

911
01:18:28,452 --> 01:18:31,489
I underestimated your power and your intellect.

912
01:18:31,532 --> 01:18:35,081
I've made a donation in your name
as a peace offering,

913
01:18:36,132 --> 01:18:38,327
as a token of my apology.

914
01:18:39,972 --> 01:18:42,327
I want you to...

915
01:18:42,372 --> 01:18:44,363
Shut up.

916
01:18:44,412 --> 01:18:46,243
I want you to forgive my stupidity.

917
01:19:08,132 --> 01:19:12,762
Wherever you don't want to go
is where you will find him.

918
01:19:14,812 --> 01:19:17,770
What is it that you are afraid of, Mr. Green?

919
01:20:01,132 --> 01:20:03,726
Why are you doing this to yourself, Jake?

920
01:20:03,772 --> 01:20:05,763
It's too tight, Jake.

921
01:20:06,812 --> 01:20:08,803
We've got to get out.

922
01:20:09,812 --> 01:20:12,087
You're going to die in a tiny space, Jake.

923
01:20:16,772 --> 01:20:18,763
Have to get out.

924
01:20:21,812 --> 01:20:23,609
We're stuck, stuck.

925
01:20:23,652 --> 01:20:25,643
The walls are moving in.

926
01:20:27,332 --> 01:20:29,323
It's tight. I'm scared.

927
01:20:29,372 --> 01:20:32,330
We've got to get out. I can hear you.

928
01:20:36,332 --> 01:20:38,129
I can hear you.

929
01:20:38,172 --> 01:20:39,161
What?

930
01:20:39,212 --> 01:20:41,487
I can hear you.

931
01:20:41,532 --> 01:20:43,727
I'm onto you.

932
01:20:50,332 --> 01:20:53,051
Who takes care of the good times?

933
01:20:53,092 --> 01:20:55,731
- We're a team.
- We're best pals, Jake.

934
01:20:55,772 --> 01:20:59,765
- You want to get rid of me?
- Do you know life without me?

935
01:20:59,812 --> 01:21:03,487
- No. Because it doesn't...
...exist.

936
01:21:03,532 --> 01:21:05,284
- Do they talk about me, Jake?
- No.

937
01:21:05,332 --> 01:21:07,323
Because I don't exist.

938
01:21:07,372 --> 01:21:11,490
- Tell all your friends about me then, Jake?
- I protect you and I control you.

939
01:21:11,532 --> 01:21:13,523
I say do, you obey.

940
01:21:13,572 --> 01:21:16,325
- If I say you're scared...
...you're scared.

941
01:21:16,372 --> 01:21:19,364
You've been listening to the other side,
haven't you, Jake?

942
01:21:19,412 --> 01:21:22,404
- Listening to people who want to hurt you.
- New people. New.

943
01:21:22,452 --> 01:21:24,443
Not old friends like me.

944
01:21:24,492 --> 01:21:28,929
People you shouldn't trust. Not me. I've been
your friend forever, since the beginning.

945
01:21:28,972 --> 01:21:31,964
Get rid of them, Jake, forever.
They're the enemy, not me.

946
01:21:32,012 --> 01:21:35,049
They're new, I'm old. I stay, they go.

947
01:21:35,092 --> 01:21:37,526
I say you do.

948
01:21:37,572 --> 01:21:38,641
You do.

949
01:21:38,692 --> 01:21:40,683
You're weak without me, weak.

950
01:21:40,732 --> 01:21:42,450
It's us against them, Jake.

951
01:21:42,492 --> 01:21:44,926
It's us against them.

952
01:21:44,972 --> 01:21:47,281
I'm coming to get you.

953
01:21:47,332 --> 01:21:49,971
You want to get rid of me?
You want to make an enemy out of me?

954
01:21:50,012 --> 01:21:52,082
You want to get rid of me, do you?

955
01:21:52,132 --> 01:21:53,645
Do you?

956
01:21:53,692 --> 01:21:56,126
You want to get rid of me, me, me, me?

957
01:22:10,852 --> 01:22:13,366
Still here, Jake?

958
01:22:13,412 --> 01:22:16,722
How long have I looked after you?

959
01:22:16,772 --> 01:22:18,842
You can't win this one without me.

960
01:22:20,452 --> 01:22:22,966
